      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "That the best is none too good\nin the way of horseflesh for the\nSpokane Interstate Fair is shown\nby the letter just received by the\nfair management from G. NJ. Will\nson of Wilbur, Wash, a regular\nexhibitor at the fair, who is now\nin Liverpool, England. Mr., Wilson\nasks to have space reserved as\nusual for his exhibit, and adds that\nhe has just purchased some of the\nfinest specimens of the draft stall\nlion to be obtained In the English\nmarket\n\n\nc.. p. Kizer of Harrisburg, Ore,\nwrites that he has arranged to have\ntwenty Oxford Down sheep in the\nfair exhibit II. Gardiner, Anaconda,\nMont, plans to exhibit fine herd\nof Hereford and Holstein cattle. A.\ng. Mills, Ferry. Wash, will bring\nten beautiful Holstein cows."
    }
